RELEASE 2 (Kickstart 1.x Bug-Fix)
---------------------------------

1. 1.x-Bug
----------

The Trainer should work on 1.x machines now. I used dos.RunCommand to
start frontier in the first version which is a 2.0-Function (V36).

Now the trainer's behaviour has changed:

Running from OS-1.x :

 dos.CreateProc to start frontier
 sends a imitated WBStartupMessage, because Frontier thinks that it
 was started from workbench (CreateProc does not create a cli-environement)

 Very hacky but working! 

Running from OS-2.x/3.x :

 dos.CreateNewProc to start frontier from a safe cli-environement, no
 tricks and hacks

 Should even work on future kickstart-versions

Thanks to Gary Streeter and to Willem Dijkstra for reporting this bug.

2. Frontier-exit-bug
--------------------

A patch exists which allows you to quit frontier. Now the trainer supports
this ability and quits too.

Thanks to Erik Gerl for mentioning this.


