INSTALLATION
------------

This is a very simple task because the programm does not need to make any
modifications on the original frontier programm. All what you have to do is
to start frontier through the trainer.

Make a copy of your original game and copy the file "FrntTrainer" to the
copied disk. Delete all in the startup-sequence and write
"frnttrainer frontier".
The stack command is not necessary because the trainer sets the stack
correctly (80 kB should be enough).

Now, boot from this disk and wait until the game starts.

HOW TO USE THE TRAINER
----------------------

Press the "DEL" key to activate the trainer (you will see
a short green flash). Press it again to deactivate (now
the flash will be red).

If the trainer is active following options are avaiable.

press LEFT SHIFT and

P   - Increases the number of shields

D   - Selects the next higher hyper-drive-class
      (have you known that the military drive class 4 is
      not the highest one, there is a unknown hyperdrive
      with the same jump distance as the hyperdirve class 8,
      but it uses military fuel)

S   - Selects the next ship (Wow, Longe Range Cruisers and
      Lynx Bulk Carriers are NOW avaiable and you can take
      a look at the famous thargoid ship... it looks like
      a pink frisby in space) If you want to fly a ship
      with its initial specifications just sell it and by
      it back, and you can take a look at the datas of the
      ship: thruster acceleration, crew members and so on.
      But never sell the thargoid ship - the game will
      crash!

0   - Increases the number of gun mountings (4 is the maximum).

1-4 - Selects the next larger gun on the front, the back,
      the top or the bottom turret. Please notice that there
      are different sizes of each gun type. If you want to
      change your gun type you have to press the key a few
      times.

R   - Clears the criminal records... YEAHHH I'm so clean!!!

C   - Increases the number of cabins by one.

Y   - Increases the cargo space by 100 t (up to 8000t).
Z     on english keyboards

M   - Increases money by 10'000'000 credits.

F   - Fills the internal fuel tank.

I   - Changes the ship-id to "TERROR".

A   - Press this one and shoot a ship. You will be on the next
      level in your combat rating

Q   - Same as "A" but for federal rank. Just press it and do
      a delivery mission and you will get a reputation.

W   - Same as "Q" but for your imperial rank.

REMARK: Don't forget to collect all medals by flying each mission
        type one time



press RIGHT SHIFT and

P   - Decreases the number of shields

D   - the next lower hyper drive class.

S   - the previous ship (you can even fly missiles and mines)
      Get the missile, sell it and by it back and you will fly
