I did my best to make the trainer safe, but sometimes the game will crash,
especially changing the ship on the fly is a little bit dangerous! Save
your game frequently while you are using the trainer!

Don't worry about some graphic trash that will appear some times. You can
prevent this by reducing the size of your gun.

Changing the ship upwards will cause hull damage. This happens because your
old ship's hull mass is not the same as the new one's. Frontier thinks that
the difference of both is the amount of hull damage. Increase your cargo
space and your money and buy a hull auto-repair system.

Sometimes the trainer doesn't react to your key strokes, especialy a problem 
on slow amigas. Hit the key more than one time until a white flash appears
and/or switch to a less cpu-intense screen (status, cargo list...).




